OL,3,CSeat cushion from the Titanic expected
OL,4,Cto fetch up to #180,000 at auction
OL,6,FA seat cushion from one of the
OL,7,FTitanic's lifeboats is expected to
OL,8,Ffetch up to #180,000 at auction later
OL,9,Fthis month.
OL,11,FIn a sale auctioneers are describing
OL,12,Fas a "once-in-a-lifetime opportunity"
OL,13,Ffor collectors, the cushion comes
OL,14,Fcomplete with the original Titanic
OL,15,Flifeboat plaque in the form of a White
OL,16,FStar burgee.
OL,18,FIt was originally bought by the friend
OL,19,Fof a London tea importer who drowned
OL,20,Fon the ship, when it hit an iceberg in
OL,21,Fthe North Atlantic on April 14, 1912.
OL,26,@tD@FOUtD@eO]
