PN,41404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1775412669
OL,3,CSeat cushion from the Titanic expected
OL,4,Cto fetch up to #180,000 at auction
OL,6,FThe story goes ` according to the
OL,7,Fauctioneer Andrew Aldridge ` that Mr
OL,8,FMatthews was so upset by what had
OL,9,Fhappened he bought the cushion when it
OL,10,Fwas first put up for sale by Meyer-
OL,11,FForest Corporation, a prominent
OL,12,Fsteamship supplies company.
OL,14,FA signed statement by George Meyer
OL,15,Fconfirms the item was a "Titanic
OL,16,FLifeboat Seat taken from one of the
OL,17,Fthirteen lifeboats brought here by the
OL,18,Frescue ship SS Carpathia along with
OL,19,Fthe lucky survivors picked up the next
OL,20,Fmorning".
OL,26,@wD@YOU|D@HO]
