PN,41405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1775412669
OL,3,CSeat cushion from the Titanic expected
OL,4,Cto fetch up to #180,000 at auction
OL,6,FMr Matthews bought the lot, keeping it
OL,7,Fin his offices until he passed it to
OL,8,Fhis grandson, George Matthews Byers in
OL,9,F1926. It has had two owners since Mr
OL,10,FByers sold it in 1987 and is now being
OL,11,Fsold by the anonymous owner.
OL,13,FAuctioneer Mr Aldridge said: "It is
OL,14,Funparalleled to be offering a fully
OL,15,Fprovenanced item from a Titanic
OL,16,Flifeboat complete with lifeboat plaque
OL,17,Ffor auction, it's totally
OL,18,Funprecedented.
OL,26,@uD@^OU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/6
